<h1> Data Policy </h1>

<p> Data Policy for thefusionfable.com </p>
<p> Effective Date: 10. September 2025 </p>

<p> <b> 1. Introduction </b></p>
<p> At thefusionfable.com, we prioritize transparency and the protection of your privacy. This policy explains how we collect, use, store, and protect your data when you use our website and other apps such as the fridge photo analysis service fridgy.</p>

<p> <b> 2. Data We Collect</b></p>
<p> When you upload a photo of your fridge or your ingredients at disposal, we collect:

<p><i>Fridge Photos </i>: Images you upload for ingredient analysis.</p>
<p><i>Detected Ingredients</i>: Ingredients identified in your photos by OpenAI’s AI gpt-4-turbo model.</p>
<p><i>Usage Data</i>: Information about how you interact with our service (e.g., timestamps, IP addresses for security).</p>
<p><i>Email Address</i>: For identification and log-in purpose.</p></p>


<p> <b> 3. How We Use Your Data</b></p>
<p> <i>Fridge Photos</i></p>

<p> Your photos are uploaded to Cloudinary, a third-party cloud storage service, for processing and storage.
We use these photos only to detect ingredients via OpenAI’s AI models.
Photos are stored in Cloudinary and referenced in our database to provide you with recipe suggestions.</p>

<p> <i>OpenAI Analysis</i></p>

We send your fridge photos to OpenAI’s API to detect ingredients using AI.
OpenAI processes the image only for ingredient detection and does not store or use your photos for any other purpose.
The detected ingredients are saved in our database to provide you with recipe suggestions.</p>

<p> <i>Usage Data</i></p>

<p> We use anonymized usage data to improve our service (e.g., tracking feature popularity).</p>


<p> <b> 4. Data Storage and Security</b></p>

<p> <p><i>Cloudinary</i>: Fridge photos are stored securely on Cloudinary’s servers. Cloudinary complies with GDPR and other data protection regulations.</p>
<p><i>Database</i>: We store references to your photos (e.g., URLs) and detected ingredients in our database, hosted on Heroku.</p>
<p><i>OpenAI</i>: Photos are sent to OpenAI’s API for analysis and are not stored by OpenAI after processing.</p>
<p><i>Heroku</i>: Our application and database are hosted on Heroku, which provides secure infrastructure and compliance with industry standards.</p></p>


<p><b> 5. Data Retention</b></p>

<p><p><i>Fridge Photos</i>: Stored in Cloudinary until you delete them or close your account.</p>
<p><i>Detected Ingredients</i>: Saved in our database to provide recipe suggestions. You can delete this data at any time by contacting us.</p>
<p><i>Usage Data</i>: Retained for up to 12 months for analytics.</p></p>


